<plot>Oswald is at the dentist. A tooth being pulled hangs on tight. Just then, the radio reports "Old King Cole has the blues" and Oswald races off in his car. He gathers up a collection of comics: 'Charles Chaplin' (qv), 'Stan Laurel' (qv), 'Oliver Hardy' (qv), etc. At the castle, they start singing off-kilter versions of Mother Goose rhymes, with 'Al Jolson' (qv) in a blackface routine, and the king is quickly cheered up. Laurel &amp; Hardy haul in a large pile of pies, and an all-out fight breaks out. The jester, who has been getting jealous of Oswald, kidnaps him during the fight and hauls him into a dungeon, submitting him to various tortures, where we discover that the real torture has been the dentist pulling the tooth all along.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?576132</url></doc>
